  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6875",
  "title": "fix(nextjs): prevent infinite loading when search client fails",
  "body": "## Summary\r\nThis PR fixes issue #6525 where the Next.js InstantSearch app would hang indefinitely during SSR when the search client fails (e.g., no network connection, API timeout, or server unavailable).\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n- Add 30-second timeout for SSR search operations to prevent infinite waiting\r\n- Add error handlers for search client failures in both composition and standard clients\r\n- Introduce `ssrSearchFailed` flag to track when SSR search fails and skip result injection\r\n- Add error listeners for helper and derived helper error events\r\n- Wrap all SSR operations in try-catch blocks to ensure graceful degradation\r\n- Make SSR results truly optional - the app continues to render even when search fails\r\n\r\n## Impact\r\nBefore this fix, if the search API was unreachable during SSR, the Next.js app would hang indefinitely, resulting in a poor user experience and potentially server timeouts.\r\n\r\nAfter this fix, the app gracefully handles connection failures and continues to render the page without SSR results, allowing client-side hydration to work normally once the connection is restored.\r\n\r\nFixes #6525\r\n\r\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
